This paper deals with signal reconstruction, which is a common problem in computer vision and image processing. The specific application of the proposed approach is image magnification, which falls under the computer vision subfield of image processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. 

The paper also discusses the use of iterative algorithms and optimization methods, which are common in the subfields of information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). 

Additionally, the paper mentions the use of low memory and computational costs, which suggests a focus on efficient algorithms and numerical methods. This could fall under the subfields of multimedia (cs.MM) or numerical analysis (cs.NA).
